rComments: An okay prof, doesn't do much outside of reading and writing her lesson plan on the chalkboard. She could explain concepts better as she is writing them down-- she often just says out loud what she's writing down, but does not explain the process behind it unless asked. Great Quercus resources tho!

Great prof to have for first year math. Meng cares a lot about her subject and her students and is always willing to stay behind after class to answer questions and help everyone out. Lectures are very informative and worth going to.

Meng is a great professor. You are always excited to go to her lectures because she explains the subject very well. My semester would have been incomplete without her class. The only downside is that you have to get used to her accent, which was not a problem for me.
Although Meng has an accent, once you get past it, she teaches very well. She explains concepts at a reasonable rate. She understands what it is like being a student in that class.
